## Common Issues

| Error                         | Cause                                   | Fix                                                  |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Permission denied (publickey) | Public key missing or wrong permissions | Check `authorized_keys` and file permissions         |
| Connection refused            | SSH service not running                 | `sudo systemctl start ssh`                           |
| java not found                | Java missing on agent                   | Install OpenJDK 17                                   |
| Host key verification failed  | Host key not trusted                    | Configure known hosts or manually trust the host key |
| Timeout                       | Port 22 blocked                         | Check firewall or cloud security group               |

---

### Best Practices

* Use SSH key authentication only; avoid password authentication for Jenkins.
* Create a dedicated `jenkins` user on the agent.
* Disable root SSH login.
* Restrict port 22 to the Jenkins controller's IP.
* Keep Java updated on both controller and agent.
* Use host key verification rather than disabling it to protect against man-in-the-middle attacks. ([Jenkins][3])

